<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-19T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-19T22:00:00-05:00" n="576" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/5507:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-19T23:00:00-04:00">May 19,
                                    1942—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>98. Your 221, May 15 and 195, May 5. Department is taking up with other
                            interested agencies of this Government the question of making specific
                            proposals to General Orgaz. You may inform him that his note of April 30
                            is receiving our active consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>